2. Way longer than I really should have, but that's mostly because testinng and
debugging with the CPU emulator is an absolute nightmare.

3. If I had the time, I would go through an extensive refactoring process, but
that's always how I feel looking back at a project in hindsight.

4. Building this program requires a C compiler to be available on the system
path (aliased to `cc`) which supports the C17 and POSIX.1-2008 standards
(tested on Linux with GCC 13.2.1 and Clang 17.0.6). No other dependencies.
